text: Oreta identata is a moth in the family Drepanidae. It was described by Watson in 1961. It is found on Sulawesi. The wingspan is 37–41.6 mm for males and 37.4–45.6 mm for females. Adults are similar to Oreta griseotincta and Oreta carnea.Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) (Entomology) 10 (8) : 336 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1961 Category:Drepaninae
title: Oreta identata
